  abstract={We show that multigrid ideas can be used to reduce the computational complexity of estimating an expected value arising from a stochastic differential equation using Monte Carlo path simulations. In the simplest case of a Lipschitz payoff and a Euler discretisation, the computational cost to achieve an accuracy of O ((epsilon)) is reduced from O ((epsilon) -3 ) to O ((epsilon) -2 (log (epsilon)) 2 ). The analysis is supported by numerical results showing significant computational savings.},
